## Existing Pseudocode "Standards" (Loose)

There are several conventions, but **no universal standard** - which is actually great for your project!

### **Academic/Textbook Styles:**
```
// Cormen (Algorithms textbook)
for i = 1 to n
    if A[i] > max
        max = A[i]

// Knuth style  
begin
    set x ‚Üê 0
    while x < n do
        increment x
end

// Structured English
FOR each item in the list
    IF item is greater than threshold THEN
        add item to results
    ENDIF
ENDFOR
```

### **Industry Variations:**
- **NASA/Defense**: Very formal, numbered steps
- **Agile**: More conversational, user-story style
- **Education**: Varies wildly by instructor

## Your Opportunity: Design Your Own Standard

Since there's no dominant standard, you can create one **optimized for your IDE experience**!

### **Design Principles for "Codeable" Pseudocode:**

#### **1. Familiar Code Symbols** (for syntax highlighting)
```
SET balance = 0
FOR user IN users {
    IF user.isActive {
        balance += user.accountValue
    }
}
RETURN balance
```

#### **2. Consistent Keyword Patterns** (for autocomplete)
```
// Control structures
IF/THEN/ELSE/ENDIF
FOR/EACH/IN/ENDFOR  
WHILE/DO/ENDWHILE
SWITCH/CASE/DEFAULT/ENDSWITCH

// Actions
SET/TO/EQUALS
ADD/REMOVE/UPDATE
CALL/RETURN
PRINT/LOG/DEBUG
```

#### **3. Visual Hierarchy** (for code folding)
```
FUNCTION calculateTax(income) {
    SET taxRate = 0

    IF income > 50000 {
        SET taxRate = 0.25
    } ELSE {
        SET taxRate = 0.15
    }

    RETURN income * taxRate
}
```

